name: Anzar (Anẓar)
shortLoreBlurb: Anzar (Anẓar) is a deity from Berber/Amazigh associated with rain, fertility. Appeased for safe passage and rains.
overlapsLinks: Manannán (Celtic), Naga (India/SE Asia), Poseidon (Greek), Tangaroa (Polynesia), Yemaya (Yoruba)
